\n<div class=\"sqs-image-shape-container-element\n\n              has-aspect-ratio\n            \"><\/p>\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"thumb-image\" src=\"https:\/\/heyciara.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/10\/image-asset-65-scaled.jpeg\" alt=\"\" data-image=\"https:\/\/heyciara.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/10\/image-asset-65-scaled.jpeg\" data-image-dimensions=\"2305x3160\" data-image-focal-point=\"0.5,0.5\" data-load=\"false\" data-image-id=\"5804f6873e00be3c82c0ba87\" data-type=\"image\"><\/p>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/figure>\n<\/div>\n<p>Happy Monday friends! Today, I am sharing some photos from my time spent in London. Thankfully, the weather was perfect for the short time that I was there. Sunny skies &amp; light winds &#8211; a contrast to London&#8217;s typical rainy weather. Of course, I visited some of London&#8217;s well known tourist attractions like Big Ben, Westminster Abbey, and Buckingham palace. Even though it&#8217;s to ideal to avoid overcrowded tourist spots, there are some attractions that must be seen. Thanks to London&#8217;s diverse population, we enjoyed amazing local Indian &amp; Caribbean eats. Since London is such a big city, I know that there is so much more to see. I can&#8217;t wait to return and dive deeper into the culture.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Happy Monday friends! Today, I am sharing some photos from my time spent in London. Thankfully, the weather was perfect for the short time that I was there. Sunny skies &amp; light winds &#8211; a contrast to London&#8217;s typical rainy weather. Of course, I visited some of London&#8217;s well known tourist attractions like Big Ben, [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":3,"featured_media":284,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"_monsterinsights_skip_tracking":false,"_monsterinsights_sitenote_active":false,"_monsterinsights_sitenote_note":"","_monsterinsights_sitenote_category":0,"